communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Park District Play email log
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Records sufficient to show the following email logs: 

A log of all emails to/from play@chicagoparkdistrict.com from April 1, 2024 through the date this request is processed. 

The logs should include but not be limited to: sender, recipient(s), date, time, subject line, and attachment name.

Please include emails where play@chicagoparkdistrict.com is cc'ed and bcc'ed and provide this log in an .xls format.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Alexandra Gelzin

title: University of Texas System Regents - April 2024 Protest Communications

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: University of Texas System Regents - April 2024 Protest Communications
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any communications (including, but not limited to, emails, text messages, social media messages, letters, memoranda, or any other form of correspondence or communication) to or from any officer of the Board of Regents on April 23, 24, or 25, 2024.

Please also note that this request seeks public records wherever they may be found, including on devices or networks owned or operated by private parties. For example, if an employee uses a personal cell phone or social media account to conduct public business, records created, maintained, or held on the phone or account are public records subject to this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

communications.subject: Confirmation Receipt
communications.communication: The University of Texas System has received your request for information and will respond in a timely manner as required by Section 552.221 of the Texas Government Code.   System’s hours of normal operation are from 8:00am to 5:00pm Monday through Friday.  If your request was submitted after business hours (after 5 pm but before midnight) it is considered received the next business day.
